Install python if not exists

Install pip or pip 3
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get -y install python3-pip

Install django
sudo pip3 install django


Starting a project

Create main project directory or navigate to location
USE: mkdir {to make directory} or cd {to navigate to directory}

Create the app
django-admin startporject {project name}


Create an app or module {sections of the application}
python3 manage.py startapp {modules}


Start server
python3 manage.py runserver



Installing MySQL database-extenstion
sudo apt-get install python3-mysqldb

Goto to setting and scroll down to databases
'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.sqlite3',  {sqllite3 =mysql}
'NAME': os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'db.sqlite3'), {NAME':DBNAME}
'USER':'USERNAME',
'PASSWORD': 'PASSWORD',
'HOST': '', {blank is default}
'PORT':'' {blank is default}


Connect the database 
python3 manage.py migrate



